Aim
To develop an Android application that demonstrates drawing basic graphic primitives such as Line, Rectangle, Circle, Oval, and Text on the screen using a custom View class and Canvas in Java.

Algorithm
1. Start Android Studio and create a new Android project.
2. Create MainActivity that extends AppCompatActivity.
3. In the onCreate() method:
Call EdgeToEdge.enable(this).
Create an object of custom class MyClass.
Set it using setContentView(view).
4. Create a custom class MyClass that extends View.
5. Declare a Paint object for color, style, and stroke width.
6. Initialize the Paint object in the constructor.
7. Override onDraw(Canvas canvas) method.
8. Inside onDraw() draw shapes:
drawLine() → draw a line
drawRect() → draw a rectangle
drawCircle() → draw circles
drawOval() → draw an oval
drawText() → display text
9. Run the application on an emulator or Android device.
10. The screen shows graphic primitives like line, rectangle, circle, oval, and text.
